Filename : README

********************************************************************************************************


		C - Project "ADDRESS BOOK" application

	Address Book is a small application written in C language. 
	It keeps track of names and telephone/mobile numbers and e-mail addresses. 

********************************************************************************************************

C files : Total 4 C files are there.

1. abk_main.c : It is main file containig the main function.

2. abk_fileops.c : This file containing the fuction related to file for example load the data from the file and 
		  save the data to the file.

3. abk_menus.c : This file containing the fucntion related to user interface and data processing.

4. abk_log.c : This file containg the function related to printing the error in display as well as in log file.


Header files : Only one header file is there.

1. abk.h : This header file containing the all #define, enums for the status and stucture definations.


>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>  How to compile the code <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

	To compile the code just type make. It will generate the one Output file named "abk". 


>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>   How to run application <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<


	Run the executeble file "abk" (Example :  ./abk ) and don't pass any command line argument to the 
	applicarion.
		   


